ssibilidade em ambientes, e sistemas de comunicação de instituições de ensino superior."	"Acessibilidade;Deficiência visual;Instituições de Ensino Superior;Fatores Humanos;Design;Processos de Interação"	"The accessibility is a quality that is still under-considered in design projects but increasingly necessary in different ways of interaction between humans and systems. There are many approaches at present intended to universalize methods to design accessible products, systems, and environments for people with disability. Design projects are frustrated when is verified the need to consider the peculiarity of each disability, that is a requirement to produce products to be in fact effective, efficient, and bring satisfaction to these specific users. The Ergonomics presents methods and techniques for the investigation that are strong allies in design that aims produce accessibility for human processes. It is possible to observe that where lack accessibility; such methods were not considered at some stage of design process. It can be verified by the routine of people with visual impairment that can present different functional necessities inside this scope. This dissertation brings in its content all the work of research developed, that aimed to verify the accessibility for people with visual impairment on the process of transition to higher education. Were applied for the investigation methods techniques based on Ergonomics and Human Factors, in an active-research to produce data, that later were analyzed under the consideration of approaches in Design that are focused on accessibility. The results show up points where the Ergonomics need to be considered on the evaluation of human processes of people with visual impairment, to design Accessibility in environments and communication systems of Higher education institutions."	"Accessibility;Visual Impairment;Higher Education Institutions;Human Factors;Design;Interaction Processes"		"0"	"PORTUGUES"	"PUC-Rio"	"Design e So